	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: Bad Groups</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11"></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, May 21st 12:26 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=/db/poster.html?user=157411><span id= >Daelonus</span></a><br><span id=notbold>25 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&nbsp;&nbsp; Few things tick me off more than greedy peeps rolling for a class/race/diety specific item that they cannot POSSIBLY use.  If there is anyone in the group who is that specific class that the item requires they and only they should get it.  The only exception I can see to this is if they already have something vastly superior and will simply sell, in which case everyone should just roll for it.  Case in point, my best friend(in RL and in EQ)is a 53 Champion who sadly is still wearing a Crafted BP. One day while in Velk's he rolled for Barbed Ringmail twice and both times lost to a pure caster, AND got kicked out of the group he was in for bitching.  Personally I think this is bit messed up, but thats just my 2cp.<br><br>Happy Hunting All :)</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Daelonus Shadowstar<br>57 Outrider of &lt;Ashen Rage&gt;<br>The Seventh Hammer<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=361804" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=361804</a></td></tr>
